Nepal’s land borders are closed to third country nationals and international flights are suspended until at least 31 May.
If you cannot leave Nepal at this time, see advice on staying in Nepal during coronavirus
Flights
Booking for UK special flights for British tourists, short term visitors and their direct dependants to return to the UK has now closed. There are currently no further special flights from Nepal.
There are currently no commercial options available to leave Nepal. The British Embassy Kathmandu is in contact with airlines, the Nepali authorities and other governments to make sure commercial options for returning to the UK are available as soon as possible.
This travel advice will be updated with further information on any future special flights and other options to leave Nepal as soon as this is available. Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British Embassy on Twitter and Facebook.
Your journey home
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air.
If you’re returning home before 8 June, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others. From 8 June there will be new rules for entering the UK.
